result.name: Mei Gui Yuan

reviews.text:
One of our favorite all-you-can-eat veggie places. They offer meat-free local no-gimmick dishes which make me feel like home. 
Wish to highlight their dessert options this time: they are all egg- and milk-free! *vegan!* been a while I hadn’t enjoyed Chinese desserts with gelatine!  
At 梅貴緣, the owner says they prepare the raw materials themselves, meaning: it’s safe for vegans / vegetarians to enjoy food and be reassured no animal was hurt to make the food. ❤️
in the photos: Chocolate cake, split pea coconut cake, water chestnut cake, sesame cake, and yum cookies.

Great vegan buffet! The owner is very nice and speaks English, so he can help you if you have questions. They are open for lunch (68hkd) and dinner (108hkd), with a variety of dishes to choose from. Definitely worth a visit :)

Went here yesterday and really loved the place! Simple, clean, with friendly staff and best of all: Tasty food! Very nice selection of vegetables and as it is a buffet you can choose anything you like. Very likely to return here soon :)
Amazing vegan Chinese Buffet in Hong Kong!  Not your usual standard buffet but real home made dishes with great variety and flavours, not greasy just simply delicious
Great vegan food choice, nice friendly staff
